= Action name = PCK.AUTOMIC_UIPATH.PUB.ACTION.START_JOB
= General description = This action starts a job manually on UiPath Orchestrator.
= Failure Conditions = * If the strategy is selected as "Specific" without specifying any Robot Id. * If Robot Ids are provided and strategy is not "Specific". * If the strategy is selected as "Robot Count" and Number of Robots is not greater than 0. * If Number of Robots is greater than 0 and strategy is not Robot Count.
= Inputs = - Process Name*: Provide the namethe process to be executed. E.g. AWI - Strategy: Specifywhich robots from the environment will be run by the process. E.g. Specific - Robot IDs: Provide the collection of ids of specific robots selected to be run by the current process. E.g. 55577 - Number of Robots: Provide the number of robots selected to be run by the current process. E.g. 0
= Behavior = * Robot Ids must be provided if Strategy is selected as "Specific". * Number of Robots must be greater than 0 if Strategy is selected as "Robot Count". * If Number of Robots is greater than the number of available robots, the job will be started for all the robots.
= Return Value = (none)
= Outputs = * Return code is 0 in case of success. * Return code is non-zero in case of failure.
= Rollback = (none)
= Logging = AE logs will be displayed in the AE report.
= Example = * For 'Specific' Strategy - Process Name*: AWI - Strategy: Specific - Robot IDs: 55577,4236 - Number of Robots: 0
* For 'Robot Count' Strategy - Process Name*: AWI - Strategy: Robot Count - Robot IDs: - Number of Robots: 2
* For 'All' Strategy - Process Name*: AWI - Strategy: All - Robot IDs: - Number of Robots: 0
